Cape Verde confirmed its first coronavirus case on Friday, the government said in a statement. The patient is a 62-year-old British citizen who entered the country on March 9 and began showing symptoms on March 16, the statement said. This development makes Cape Verde the 37th country in Africa to record confirmed cases of the novel Covid-19 coronavirus. Burkina Faso on Wednesday confirmed its first Covid-19 death, that of a high ranking government official – the first in sub-Saharan Africa. On Friday, South Africa's health minister, Zweli Mkhize, announced that its rate of coronavirus infections had risen to 202 — a 25% increase from 150 recorded on Thursday.